CSS Transforms

1. What does a CSS transform allow the developer to do to an element?
  Elements may be distorted, transformed, and rotated. 

2. Provide an example of a transform and how you could see that being used on a website.
  You could use a scale transform, that could act in the same manner as putting an element in
  a grid, instead, it is its own independ thing. 
  
CSS Transitions & Animations

1. What does a CSS transition allow the developer to do to an element?
  It allows the dev to change the appearance, and behavior of an element, whenever a stage
  change occurs. 
  
2. How does a CSS animation differ from a CSS transition?
  Transitions are good for single state changes. Animations, are good when multiple states
  are needed. 

8 simple CSS3 transitions that will wow your users

1. What are some benefits to using CSS transitions on websites?
  You can more easily format changes, have faster page speed, and have a better overall 
  UX.

2. How this topic fit in with your long-term goals?
  This topic allow tools to make the pages I create more interactive and "fun". It will also help
  my pages run smoother. 
